      <div class="msgContentFrame">Ok so after a lot of playing recently (finally hit Surplus lol) I have compliled my experiences into best way to get SP in parties: <br /> <br />1. Sacrifice 1 and Cure 1 only if more than 1 mage in party. Only use Tier II's if absolutely needed. <br />2. Stygian Spikes as often as you like (just remember that overwriting a buff <i>doesn't</i> net you SP!(ty Miayr) <br />3. Profundity + Scourge/Banish whenever its up - can net 250-300sp for just one successful hit. <br />4. Scourge/Banish when profundity is not up. <br />5. Siphon MP (not for SP gain but to keep MP up) when mob is dead (this gets you much more MP most of the time) <br />6. Spirit Dart/Phantom Dart when you get chance.(Again using Profundity here can get you a bigger hit and more SP) <br />7. Damnation/Radiance when you get the chance. <br />8. Protect and Shell during fight only if possible (does get you SP) - sometimes Protect is not needed though and can hurt SP! <br />9. ABS DEF/ACC/EVA (situational depending on mob) but I wouldnt recommend using ABS ATT because mob will hit people for less. <br />10. Dia not Bio (again depending on situation). Dia has chance of double proc similar to Scourge/Banish. <br />11. Any other debuffs you can manage that dont hurt your own SP gain - If you have time after all of the above! <br /> <br />Make sure that any other mages in your group understand these rules. <br />Make sure mele in your group dont use stun moves on mob, try to get them not to use anything that gives them HP back or DEF if you can!, and try to stop them using absorb/deplete TP moves as you want the mob to hit them with aoe! :) <br /> <br />Hope this helps and if anyone has anything to add please do - this will go into my guide at some point. <br /> <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov 19th 2010  7:40am by EdyNOTB </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="HTTP://lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=2993179" rel="external nofollow" title="lodestone.finalfantasyxiv.com/rc/character/status?cicuid=2993179">Loadstone Profile</a> <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?forum=179&amp;mid=1282291867193441649" rel="external" title="ffxiv.zam.com/forum.html?forum=179&amp;mid=1282291867193441649">Thaumaturge Guide</a> <br /> <br /><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/1229110.png" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /> <br /></div></div>
